{"id":"software-for-climate-4","editors":["nilesh@terra.do","cynthia@terra.do","sarahburgess@terra.do","shamolie@terra.do","jasmine@terra.do","jignasa@terra.do","jason@terra.do","jaime@terra.do"],"classTitle":"Emissions, global warming potentials and the global carbon cycle","index":[{"heading":"Introduction","slideId":"2"},{"heading":"Resources","slideId":"3"},{"heading":"Conclusion","slideId":"4"}],"content":[{"classId":"software-for-climate-4","slideId":"1","questionType":"media+text","slideTemplateId":"SS1","slideHeading":"Software for Climate","body":["<div>4. Energy modeling</div>\n"],"question":" ","notes":" ","multimediaType":"image","multimediaSource":" ","multimediaTitle":" ","multimedia":"http://res.cloudinary.com/terra-do/image/upload/v1691785201/Events/tjwabfsu0xyvccqxbnzv.jpg","slideType":"information","version":9,"editor":"jaime@terra.do","hints":[""],"solution":" "},{"classId":"software-for-climate-4","slideId":"2","questionType":" ","slideTemplateId":"S1","slideHeading":"Learning Objectives","body":["<div>1. Understand the categories &amp; tools for energy modeling in climate tech</div>\n\n<div>2. Produce results from an energy modeling tool</div>\n"],"question":" ","notes":" ","multimediaType":"image","multimediaSource":"https://firefly.adobe.com ","multimediaTitle":"Adobe Firefly","multimedia":"http://res.cloudinary.com/terra-do/image/upload/v1699201225/Events/x0adbvst5q5f8ebtiaxb.png","slideType":"information","version":5,"editor":"jaime@terra.do","hints":[""],"solution":" "},{"classId":"software-for-climate-4","slideId":"3","questionType":" ","slideTemplateId":"L1","slideHeading":"Resources","body":["<div>Read through at least one of of these. Here&#39;s what we recommend, in rough priority order:</div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Read pages 5-6 in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://assets.jpmprivatebank.com/content/dam/jpm-wm-aem/campaign/energy-paper-13/growing-pains-renewable-transition-in-adolescence.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Growing Pains: the Renewable Transition in Adolescence</a>,&nbsp;including the chart labeled &quot;US final energy consumption by sector and fuel&quot;.\n\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>Consider that decarbonizing our power supply has two steps:\n\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t<li>Electrify everything: all dark brown bars (&quot;Direct fossil fuels&quot;) need to change to green (&quot;direct renewables&quot;) or blue (&quot;electricity&quot;)</li>\n\t\t\t<li>Decarbonize the grid: The electricity grid has to be 100% clean (green dashed line gets to 100%!)</li>\n\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</li>\n\t\t<li>Both of these are highly complex and nuanced issues with lots of impact opportunities. Modeling is a critical part of this!</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>Listen to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.volts.wtf/p/whats-the-deal-with-interconnection\" target=\"_blank\">Volts podcast: What&#39;s the deal with interconnection queues?</a>&nbsp;(~50 min)</li>\n\t<li>Read pages 10-14&nbsp;in <a href=\"https://content.aia.org/sites/default/files/2016-04/Energy-Modeling-Design-Process-Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">An Architect&rsquo;s Guide to Integrating Energy Modeling in the Design Process</a></li>\n\t<li>Go back to the first doc, Growing Pains, and read/skim:\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>Page 15, lower half, addressing &quot;dunkelflaute&quot;</li>\n\t\t<li>Page 35: &quot;Energy in, most of the energy out&quot;&nbsp;</li>\n\t\t<li>Anything else that catches your eye. This report is full of good stuff!</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n"],"question":"text only","notes":" notes ","multimediaType":"image","multimediaSource":" ","multimediaTitle":" ","multimedia":"http://res.cloudinary.com/terra-do/image/upload/v1691785524/Events/p0wljys6f6wx2sx77zbc.jpg","slideType":"information","version":4,"editor":"jaime@terra.do","hints":[""]},{"classId":"software-for-climate-4","slideId":"4","questionType":"media+text","slideTemplateId":"L1","slideHeading":"Conclusion","body":["<div>See you in the live session!</div>\n"],"question":" ","notes":" ","multimediaType":"image","multimediaSourc